The paper discusses security vulnerabilities in Deep Neural Networks (DNNs) and proposes a resource-efficient decision-based methodology for generating imperceptible attacks. This methodology involves classification boundary estimation and adversarial noise optimization, which are relevant to several sub-categories of computer science. Specifically, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category as the paper deals with DNNs and their vulnerabilities. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also likely as the paper discusses security attacks and their mitigation. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is relevant as the proposed methodology is evaluated for image classification tasks. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper deals with machine learning models and their vulnerabilities. Finally, cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper discusses resource-constrained systems such as autonomous vehicles.
